1. PRIMARY SCREEN DATASET — Primary Human CD4+ T Cell Perturb-seq
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Source     : Marson lab (Gladstone/UCSF) and Jonathan Pritchard lab (Stanford),
             hosted on the CZI Virtual Cells Platform.
Publication: Zhu R, Dann E, Yan J, Reyes Retana J, Goto R, Guitche RC, et al.,
             Pritchard JK, Marson A. "Genome-scale perturb-seq in primary human
             CD4+ T cells maps context-specific regulators of T cell programs and
             human immune traits." bioRxiv, 2025. DOI 10.64898/2025.12.23.696273
Accession  : CZI Virtual Cell Models dataset "Primary Human CD4+ T Cell
             Perturb-seq"; processed data s3://genome-scale-tcell-perturb-seq/;
             raw sequencing GEO GSE314342 / SRA SRP643211.
License    : MIT (copyright Emma Dann, 2025), subject also to the CZI Virtual Cell
             Models Acceptable Use Policy.
Used for   : perturbation effect vectors and responder-DE knockdown vectors from
             which the redistributed per-gene aggregate statistics are derived.


2. DISEASE-REFERENCE DATASET — JIA synovial single-cell atlas (CD4 T cells)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Source     : CZ CELLxGENE Discover, collection
             10eb236d-d42d-45b8-8363-c2dcf865f388.
Publication: Knight OC, Giordano C, von Stuckrad ASL, et al. "A single-cell atlas
             of innate immunity in treatment-naive juvenile idiopathic arthritis."
             bioRxiv, 2026. DOI 10.64898/2026.05.01.716870
Companion  : Bolton C, Mahony CB, Clay E, et al. "Synovial tissue atlas in
             juvenile idiopathic arthritis reveals pathogenic niches associated
             with disease severity." Sci Transl Med, 2025;17(805):eadt6050.
             DOI 10.1126/scitranslmed.adt6050 (GEO GSE278962/278968/278969).
License    : CC-BY-4.0 (CZ CELLxGENE Discover platform license).
Used for   : the donor-paired synovium-vs-blood disease-direction vector
             (activated-memory CD4), redistributed as per-gene aggregate log2FC.


